      <section eId="sec_CCP-2083">
        <num>CCP 2083</num>
        <heading>2083. Â Judgments appealable</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCP-2083__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>A final judgment is appealable in all causes in which appeals are given by law, whether rendered after hearing, by default, or by reformation under Article 1814.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-2083__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>In reviewing a judgment reformed in accordance with a remittitur or additur, the court shall consider the reasonableness of the underlying jury verdict.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-2083__subsec_C">
          <num>C.</num>
          <content>
            <p>An interlocutory judgment is appealable only when expressly provided by law.
Amended by</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=111376</p>
